Uplink is a fast, secure IRC client targeting LinuxDojo.org and general
use. It speaks IRCv3 and connects with TLS by default.

Features:
 - IRCv3: message IDs, server-time, echo-message, batch, SASL PLAIN and
   EXTERNAL, reply threading, reactions, message redaction, typing
   indicators, account-tag, MONITOR, STS, chathistory
 - DCC send/receive with passive mode and transfer progress
 - SOCKS5 proxy per server
 - 55 colour themes (TOML format)
 - OS keychain for password storage
 - Desktop notifications and system tray icon

WWW: https://github.com/noderelay/UplinkIRC
